g.text: she could not, no could not stop dreaming of ink. ink, you see, was
permanent, and she wanted to leave her mark on the world. she began
by drinking ink until it poured out of her fingertips. everything she
touched, she smudged. she left her marks indelible anywhere she placed
her hands. on furniture, on pets, on lovers, on fiends. turnstiles, fences,
doorknobs, and keys. when she breathed a cloud of ink left her as steam.
